# Auth0 Configuration
# Get these from https://manage.auth0.com > Applications > Your App
AUTH0_SECRET='< generate base 64 >'
AUTH0_BASE_URL='http://localhost:3000'
AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL='https://<AUTH0-URL>.us.auth0.com'
AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=''
AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET=''

# Auth0 Token Vault for GitHub (optional)
# To enable repo browsing via Auth0:
# 1. Create a GitHub App at https://github.com/settings/apps
#    - Homepage URL: https://YOUR_AUTH0_DOMAIN.auth0.com
#    - Callback URL: https://YOUR_AUTH0_DOMAIN.auth0.com/login/callback
#    - Permissions: Repository (read)
# 2. In Auth0 Dashboard > Authentication > Social > GitHub
#    - Enter your GitHub App Client ID and Secret
#    - Enable "Connected Accounts for Token Vault"
#    - Assign to your application
